{"questionId":"23455","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A conducting sphere has radius 48 cm. The electric potential on the surface of the sphere is&nbsp;3.4 × 10<sup>5</sup> V.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The sphere is connected by a long conducting wire to a second conducting sphere of&nbsp;radius 24 cm. The second sphere is initially uncharged.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"__IMG__/f5685d397759a5163dab3afa806e18620ef5caee.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Predict the charge on each sphere.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mfrac><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mn>48</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mfrac><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mn>24</mn></mfrac><mo>⇒</mo><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn></math>&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math> «μC»,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn></math> «μC»&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[3]</strong> marks for a bald correct answer.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"23455","referenceCode":"21N.2.HL.TZ0.7b.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Predict the charge on each sphere.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields","10.2 – Fields at work","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}